2026-04-16 12:19:28 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['cable_pair_between_power_supply_and_control_module'] hypothesis_explanation='The green LED on the power-supply module being ON shows that the 12 V source is present and correctly oriented inside that module. The red LED on the control module is designed to light only when the 12 V and 0 V lines coming from the power supply are connected with reversed polarity into the control module. Therefore, with the red LED ON and the main lamp not lighting even when the switch is closed, the most likely cause is that the two cables between the power-supply module and the control module are swapped (i.e., the 12 V and 0 V leads are interchanged at their quick-connect terminals). Correcting this cable polarity should extinguish the red indicator and allow the load-lamp circuit to function when the switch is operated.'
